Welcome to **Python Basics for Agentic AI**, a comprehensive, beginner-friendly GitHub repository designed to teach you the fundamental Python skills necessary to succeed in modern Agentic AI and Large Language Model (LLM) application development.

We go from zero-to-hero on core concepts, focusing on the syntax and structures most relevant for data handling, control flow, and external tool interaction‚Äîall prerequisites for building intelligent agents.

---

## üöÄ Learning Path & Modules

This repository is structured as a progressive bootcamp. Complete the modules in order:

| Module | Title | Key Concepts for AI |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **01** | Introduction to Python | Syntax foundation, Code Execution |
| **02** | Google Colab Setup | Environment setup, Dependency management |
| **03** | Data Types & Variables | Data representation (int, float, bool, str), State management |
| **04** | Operators | Logic & Comparisons (essential for conditional actions in agents) |
| **05** | Keywords | Reserved words, basic function definition (`def`) |
| **06** | Strings & Casting | Text processing, Data serialization/deserialization |
| **07** | Exercises & Quizzes | Practical application & reinforcement |

---

## ‚úÖ Prerequisites

* **Motivation:** A desire to learn programming and enter the world of AI/LLMs.
* **Web Browser:** Access to Google Chrome, Firefox, or Safari for using Google Colab.
* **Optional:** A basic understanding of what a "program" is.

**No prior Python knowledge is required!**

