## üíª Running the Code

The primary method for running the code is **Google Colaboratory (Colab)**, which requires zero setup on your machine.

1.  **Open the Notebook:** Click on any `notebook.ipynb` file in the repository.
2.  **Run in Colab:** Click the "Open in Colab" badge at the top of the file preview.
3.  **Execute Cells:** Click the play button next to each code cell or use `Shift + Enter`.

Alternatively, you can clone the repository and run the Python files locally.

```bash
git clone [https://github.com/your-github-username/python-basics-agentic-ai.git](https://github.com/your-github-username/python-basics-agentic-ai.git)
cd python-basics-agentic-ai/03_data_types_and_variables
python examples.py
